page.title: 03ECOLOGYII
page.content: THESE HEDGES & WOODLANDS PROVIDE FOOD & SHELTER DEER,FOX,STOATS,HEDGEHOGS,BANK VOLES,SHREWS,WEASELS,RABBITS,FIELD MICE BROWN RATS AND LESS COMMON BADGERS.A CHINESE SPECIES OF DEER CALLED MUNTJAK ARE RESIDENT HERE AFTER ESCAPING FROM THE NEARBY SAFARI PARK AT WOBURN.ROE & FALLOW ALSO COMMON.BIRDS ARE ABUNDANT: BLACKBIRD,THRUSH,SPARROWS,ROBINS,TITS, MAGPIES,GREENFINCH,GOLDFINCH,CHAFFINCH, CUCKOO AND OWLS.HERONS INHABIT AN ISLAND NEAR TYRINGHAM BRIDGE.ALSO SWANS DUCKS COOTS AND MOORHENS.2/3 PAIRS OF GREAT CRESTED GREBE.SOME KINGFISHERS. FISH IN RIVER OUSE INCLUDE ROACH,CARP PERCH,DACE,CHUBB,PIKE,MINNOW,BULLHEAD BREAM,GUDGEON AND TENCH.FROGS AND TOADS ARE ON THE INCREASE.DRAGON AND DAMSEL FLIES.BUTTERFLIES INCLUDE LARGE & SMALL WHITE,GREEN-VEINED WHITE,MEADOW BROWN, WALL BROWN,HEDGE BROWN,SMALL HEATH, SPECKLED WOOD,COMMON BLUE,SMALL COPPER.
